state.unicode: Once a powerful and fearsome ruler, Priam has grown concerned with his legacy in his old age. The king of Troy is grooming his two favourite sons to inherit the throne after him. If you are to rule, you must compete with your sibling for your father's benevolent assent for your ascent to the throne. In addition to fulfilling his requests before your brother does, you can sabotage your rival's efforts to undermine your father's opinion of him. Remember, only the most worthy will be named King Priam's rightful heir!\n{{tr:troy_main_fm_priam_heir_no_war_on_priam}}

uientry.unicode: When a given milestone is reached, the top two objectives will be locked and replaced with two new ones. Make sure to complete them quickly before they disappear!

If Priam ultimately prefers you to your brother, he will name you his successor and abdicate the throne in your favour. At that point, you will immediately confederate both Troy and your brother's faction, effectively gaining control over both as the undisputed king of all the Trojans.
You must wait for the cooldown period to end before you can use sabotage again.

state.unicode: Wise Priam's attention is preoccupied with Troy's needs. His advisors will inform us of his will when the time comes.

uientry.unicode: Your father is a wise ruler, but he is also known for his fickleness. Should the timer on this mission reach zero, Priam will withdraw his request and issue a new one instead.
